    "created_at": "2016-09-06T16:12:35Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-09-06T16:12:35Z",
    "body": "There are a number of things that Electron doesn't do for application authors that are considered \"standard practice\" for some types of applications on some platforms. For reference, see [all the comments in the sample code in the Quick Start guide](http://electron.atom.io/docs/tutorial/quick-start/#write-your-first-electron-app). Because we can't know ahead of time what type of application people have in mind, we don't feel it is appropriate to make those decisions on behalf of application authors.\n\nAdditionally, it is common for application frameworks to not do this on behalf of application authors. Even OS X applications have to [do this for themselves](https://developer.apple.com/library/mac/documentation/Cocoa/Conceptual/WinPanel/Tasks/SavingWindowPosition.html), it doesn't happen by default.\n\nAs such, as was [stated previously](https://github.com/electron/electron/issues/526), we have no API for this and no plans to create one.\n\nThanks very much for your feedback and interest in Electron!\n"
  },
